Training from aws with devops.

*Lunch ec2 master and slave
*<hostnamectl set-hostname master> in master then getin bash <exec bash>.

*Enable the password authentication in slave machines location is <nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config> then restart the ssh <systemctl restart ssh>

*Install ansible <apt-get install ansible -y> in master then

*Need to create SSH key <ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096> -b (bits) 4096 is an bits for encrption.

		-Specifies the no. of bits for the key size. These were 1024, 2048 earlier.

		-2048 * 2 = 4096 is considered strong. Hence the recommended key size.for ssh keygen.

*after created key it there in <cd~/.ssh/> location.

*need to create new user <adduser <name>> in slave and To verify user created or not nano /etc/passwd

*we need to copy the key from master to slave into this location <cd ~/.ssh/> then <ssh-copy-id username@ip_address> 
 
	for example <ssh-copy-id test@172.31.1.1>

*after user created we need to enable password anthrndicatin in this location <nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config> 

* Need to remove <Passwordauthentication No> change like <Passwordauthentication yes>

* And <PermitRootLogin Prohibed-password> 
			change to <PermitRootLogin yes> -> we connect remote while providing username using root user like ( ssh -i root@ipaddress) to take remote for other server.
* after that <systemctl restart ssh>


*then we need to copy ssh keygen to slave machine from master in to this location <cd ~/.ssh/>

*for check all machines ping <ansible all -i inventory -m ping> or <ansible all -m ping> and 
this cmd will display all root files <ansible all -m command -a "ls -l/">

