*In ansible states

-->Install - present
-->uninstall - absent
-->start -started
-->stop - stopped
-->restart -restarted

for httpd install
->ansible all -i slaves.txt -m apt -a "name=httpd state=present" -b 
-b -> become it means sudo user superior user.

for nginx install with playbooks.
-->ansible all -i slaves.txt -m apt -a "name=nginx state=present" --become --ask-become-pass
-->ansible-playbook -i slaves.txt nginx.yml --ask-become-pass



--> this cmd for install apache2 = ansible all -i slaves.txt -m apt -a "name=apache2 state=present" -become --ask-become-pass
--> this cmd for start apache2   = ansible all -i slaves.txt -m service -a "name=apache2 state=started" -become --ask-become-pass
--> this cmd for copy one file from master to slave = ansible all -i slaves.txt -m copy -a "src=/home/ec2-user/index.html dest=/var/www/html/index" -become --ask-become-pass

